			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-09-12T14:20:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2013/07/dissecting-a-wordpress-brute-force-attack.html#comment-3000">September 12, 2013</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Sadly I found this article because it appears that my wordpress site might have been attacked by this. I can&#8217;t log in. When I try, I get the word FORBIDDEN and nothing else on the screen. My website is still up and from what I can tell, nothing has changed from a visitor&#8217;s perspective. I just don&#8217;t know how to clean this up. I like what perezbox says below about disabling the theme and plugin editor. I&#8217;m not using Twenty Twelve, although it is still a theme loaded on the site. Its just disabled. And as soon as I get it cleaned up, I will use the list of 1 &#8211; 4 things above to deter such activity in the future. HELP PLEASE!</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

